penelope spheeris is best known for her work as the director of classic 90’s films including “wayne’s world”, “black sheep”, and “the little rascals”. before her big break in hollywood she was a recognized documentary filmmaker, known for her work in the punk and metal music scenes. 
our podcast takes us through the people she’s crossed paths with in her career including mike myers, bob & harvey weinstein, chris farley, donald trump, david spade, lorne michaels, sharon osbourne & ozzfest, roseanne barr, mel brooks, richard pryor, dana carvey, rob lowe, albert brooks, penny marshall, rob reiner, and jon cryer.

text:
"perse viktimat e dhunes seksuale nuk i raportojne rastet e dhunes ?:
pertej kornizes sone sociale , viktimat e dhunes seksuale pasi akti ka ndodhur perjetojne nje gjendje te renduar psikologjike , ndjenjat e para qe ata perjetojne jane turpi, mllefi dhe faji. ne fjale te tjera ndjenjat e abuzuesit projektohen mbi viktimen . ne pjesen me te madhe te rasteve dhunuesit seksuale jane persona te njohur per viktimen , shoke , familjare ose dikush qe viktima frekuentonte . kjo e ben me te veshtire dhe me pak te besueshme viktimen ne rast raportimi dhe e le ate ne nje gjendje te pashprese. turpi eshte nje reagim psikologjik i pranishem ne pjesen me te madhe te rasteve te abuzimit , ky i fundit mund te intensifikohet ne rastet e shoqerive me patriarkale dhe maskiliste.
"perse viktima nuk reagon gjate aktit ?"
truri njerezor eshte i programuar te mbroje vetveten , ne rastet e dhunes seksuale viktima perjeton shok dhe kjo frike con ne nje gjendje te quajtur "palevizshmeri tonike". tonic immobility sikurse njihet ne anglisht eshte reagimi i trurit njerezor perpara nje rreziku te paperballueshem , ne kete rast trupi paralizohet dhe viktima mbetet fizikisht prezente por psikologjikosht e disociuar nga akti. nje trup i paralizuar nuk mund te reagoje . 
se fundmi , perdhunimi perben veper penale. liria seksuale dhe shendeti seksual jane te drejta kushtetuese . cdo raport jo konsensual , i kryer ne rrethanat e kanosjes , kercenimit apo tjeter perben veper te denueshme penalisht . deshira seksuale eshte plotesisht njerezore.
lexoni, informohuni , clirohuni nga tabute dhe nese mundeni .. shume me vone.. gjykoni ! #rapevictim #malechauvinism #feminism #myvoice #metoo #realmenarefeminists #pinkmovement @hannah_288

text:
i n t u i t i v e l y -  g u i d e d -  r e t r e a t 
the greatest love of all is the one with yourself.  when you feel like you’ve lost the connection, just spend time seeking out moments that make your heart swell - where your eyes well up from the simplicity of connection without words. to be with people who truly experience emotion and connection on the same level as you, where you feel safe and able to expand into who you are on a soul level. there was deep healing, trust and release happening this weekend and it was really powerful. simple yet powerful. 
this was my first retreat and i trusted completely in my intuition, did away with the workbooks and schedules of how the weekend was going to pan out. i simply shared my experience with others which allowed them to do the same. moving from moment to moment, one step at a time. it was beautiful and profound. i felt vulnerable to work in this way especially with 2 well respected coaches attending but it empowered me to do it authentically and in the way that felt true to my heart. 
in truth i invited them all to an experience and the way it unfolded was perfect because what we all have in common is a desire to lead from the heart 💓 
thank you ladies for the love, the friendships and the experiences we shared. 
there were tears of grief, happiness & remembering, lots of laughter, fun, and memories made. courage brought us here, connection made us grow, love will keep us together 💝🦋 #womenofintuition #soulled #heartled #loveled #lightworker #deephealing #ancestralhealing #spiritualevolution #connections #workingwiththeelements #natureiscallingme #trust #metoo #sacredplaces #iseeyou #consciousness #collectiveconsciousness

text:
have you ever, either as a child or an adult been the unfortunate victim of a bully/bullies? #metoo
as a child, i was never bullied. i had an easy ride as far as school and other children where concerned. i was pretty tough as a child really. fast forward to well into my 20’s i found myself in a job with a narcissistic bully of a manager. you could do your job to an amazing standard but he’d pick out one very insignificant unrelated thing and use it to make you feel completely useless and deflated. sometimes i wondered if it was me, am i too sensitive? do i expect too much? am i looking for praise in a place i won’t ever get it? no. he’s a very unhappy person who believes his life is full of roses and happiness. however, if somebody’s life was full of roses and happiness, they wouldn’t feel the need to constantly put others down. racism, sexism, pessimism are just a few negative traits they could use to cause bad feeling around the place.
the key to not letting this affect you is to make sure you come from a place of authenticity and rawness. don’t be sucked into the drama in which they create. it’s really hard to stay positive in such a negative environment but either consider completely taking yourself away from it or develop skills to enable you to deal with it without judgement and/or expectation. ❤️
bit of a different post from me but one that needs addressing nonetheless. take care x

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
known for being outspoken and brutally honest, jami spoke about the larger issue in connection to the #alizafar v #meeshashafi sexual harassment case. “i’ve stood up really crudely against the item number culture. i spoke up against selling women in our films. ali zafar was my very good friend. i was closer to him as compared to meesha,” he recalled. “but when meesha came out with her story, i knew i had to support her. but unfortunately, we made the accused’s film a blockbuster. i’m not someone who really weighs his words before speaking. and i did exactly that. i supported meesha and the backlash that followed was problematic.”
he added, “the point is, it is extremely hard for women to come forward with such ordeals. we don’t believe them and that is what we need to change. if all the cases start to come out, majority of the showbiz industry will be in trouble.” 📝 @etribune 📸 @steermedia 📢 session: be khauf azad hai jeena mujhe moderated by @rahmamian
isn't about time we start calling a harasser, whose predatory behavior has been confirmed by several women and girls on social media, as a harasser instead of an "accused" person? what do you think? nonetheless, we must appreciate with how much maturity our media has done the coverage. 
#lahootimelo #lahootimelo2019
#metoo #jamimahmood #ibelieveher #believesurvivors
#lm2019 #lahooti #jamshoro

text:
good girls celebrate international women’s day| 08.03.19

the 8th march is international women’s day, so what better day to host a special gged event? come join us at the fabulous design museum, where we’ll be serving up searcys cuvee, delicious finger food and incredible speakers. 
tickets available from link in bio.

all guests are welcome to take a look around the permanent exhibition before moving to the kitchen where we’ll serve up delicious searcys food plus incredible speakers who’ll be giving their take on how much of their career, or life journey, was down to design - and how much was down to luck or judgement.

speakers:
dagmara kodlubanski - a director and filmmaker - currently completing her exciting film project, we still rise, in collaboration with passion pictures. we still rise is a feature length documentary about the women’s march that took place on january 21st 2017, the day after trump was inaugurated. it's a film that captures the moment the torch for #metoo was lit. (we’ll be screening a 4 minute trailer of the film on the night). 💥

the masons - maruska & donna-marie mason - are a london based photographer duo working across advertising, editorial and portraiture. inspired by people who break boundaries and are not afraid to lead the change, they explore diversity and equality in a timeless style with an edge, always pushing and allowing for their subject's personality and story to shine through. 📸 
lisa redman founded her own namesake label in 2007 having previously worked alongside betty jackson, elspeth gibson and as a textile designer for calvin klein. she now creates bespoke, contemporary womenswear with an expert team from her west london atelier. ⚡️ theme: luck, judgement or design

tickets available from link in bio
@searcyslondon @designmuseum @westillrisemovie @lisaredmanltd @themasonsofficial

text: today we are grateful for...harps. especially harps being played in the middle of central park. i was reminded of the harp tonight when i noticed the harp intro on rod stewart’s cover of “the first cut is the deepest.” which made me think of the woman i saw playing harp in the park last summer, wondering how she lugged that thing around the city, while simultaneously being enthralled by the sounds she was making. i guess there’s a reason the angels allegedly play harps in heaven. they make for a pretty enchanting soundtrack. i first appreciated the harp as a kid, since i was a huge marx brothers fan growing up. and while i loved groucho the wiseass and chico the affable scam artist, it was impossible not have a soft spot for horndog harpo, who made beautiful music on his harp—while crossing #metoo lines in just about every marx brothers movie. then again, harpo spelled backwards is oprah, so he can’t be all bad. more harp for us insomniacs! #365daysofgratitude #day43 #centralpark #nyc #harp #harpomarx #marxbrothers #oprah #music

text_retweet:
reposted from @iam_beautymartins -  now to the main story. few days of my consistent going to the library, i saw an amazingly pretty woman, always astonishingly adorned with gorgeous dresses, smiling and walking pass me each day, and it did not take long before i was introduced to her. 
it was at that point i got to realize she owned the foundation, then she said a  few words to me  that changed my perspective.  that wasn’t the end, next day, she came with a very big book, and guess what was the subject matter? “ sociology”. she gave me the book and asked me to study it and  share my experience with her, that was a turning point for me. after that book, i totally lost my interest in law and decided to become a sociologist, she helped me navigate my decision making at that time, and as if that wasn’t enough, she got really interested in my growth and started opening up her connections to me from different angles.  i cannot share my success story anywhere in the world today, without mentioning, mrs @bitebogogo ,she made me hunger and yearn for excellence, she introduced me to practically everyone i know today or i have worked with in the last 5years of my life, either directly or indirectly. i got my first internship through her foundation @keeping it real foundation.

she would create time to take me to some offices just to tell them about what i can do, mrs g, as fondly called, had so much confidence in me that some days when i felt i couldn’t do some things, she gave me reasons to go ahead and i smashed them 100% and more. at some point in my year two, she contributed to help me pay my fees, which is one thing i can never forget.

when i look back at my growth process, i cannot help but thank god i met her. she opened me up to the world and showed me the path to the woman i am becoming, i everyday i thank god that our paths crossed. she held the ladder for me to climb through and i raise her up now and always as my woman of worth- because of her, today i can boldly say: #empoweredwomenempowerothers.

i nominate @mz_juanita1 to share her empowerment story. lets spread the light.

#empoweredforsustainability

#awlcrwanda2019 - #regrann

when i look back at my growth process, i cannot help but thank god i met her. she opened me up to the world and showed me the path to the woman i am becoming, i everyday i thank god that our paths crossed. she held the ladder for me to climb through and i raise her up now and always as my woman of woh- because of her, today i can boldly say: mpoweredwomenempowerothers.

i nominate  to share her empowerment story. lets spread the light.

mpoweredforsustainability

text:
jameela jamil credits #metoo for keeping her clear of being cuddled in meetings
#
wenn/adriana m. barraza sitting for a chat with chat with human rights activist zainab salbi, 'the good place' actress also talks about singer boyfriend james blake whom she deems 'an ally' and a 'good feminist.' aceshowbiz - the #metoo movement has served up a big win for british actress and tv personality jameela jamil - she no longer has to hug executives in meetings. "the good place" star insists the anti-harassment campaign, which sprung up in the wake of the harvey weinstein sex abuse scandal in late 2017, has been good for her and she has noticed a change in hollywood. "i'm not being cuddled at the end of meetings anymore," she told yahoo news show "through her eyes", adding she hopes those in hollywood who test the new empowerment rules laid out by the #metoo movement suffer. "i would like to hope that we don't allow racists and bigots to have big parts in hollywood movies," she says. "so therefore, if you've assaulted a woman, you should just f**k off for a while." during her yahoo news chat with human rights activist zainab salbi, jamil also gushed about her boyfriend james blake, calling the singer a "good feminist." …

breaking the cycle or giving one forgiveness is not an easy thing to do. 
it benefits many but you especially. 
so for yourself let go of the unnecessary burdens and guilt we lay upon ourselves. we deserve nothing less.

name: Lenora Willette Flores
pre_proc_tweet:
"giselle" is one of the world's most famous ballets. originating in paris in 1841 - it is the story of a poor young peasant girl with a "weak" hea - giselle - who becomes the wealthy, powerful and perfidious albrecht's lover, only to be discarded by him when he decides to marry a woman from "his class." her "weak" hea breaks. she dies. 
enter the "willlis" - powerful, mystical, female ghosts who yank her out of her grave to help them find and kill albrecht on behalf of all victimized women. having all died of broken heas themselves, they only exist to seek revenge on men. is this the way? giselle's brain still resides in her hea. she can still  choose to forgive albrecht with her newly muscular and apparently undying hea and does, saving his life and her soul. this ballet is an established pa of many classical dance repeoires and is rarely drastically reimagined. akram khan's "giselle the movie" has reimagined it, creating explosive new traditions of dance and filmmaking in the process. his "giselle" is wildly innovative, emotionally riveting, visually stunning and quite the poetic piece of intercultural diffusion (the melding of traditions from one culture and as genre, to another). i enthusiastically recommend it for a few more reasons - khan has an impressive command of the hea of the story, of the history of dance, of depth psychology (issues of the unconscious and of the hea epistemology linking male/female/shadow story archetypes), of the language of music (vincenzo lamagna's score), of this zeitgeist ( weinstein et al) and of storytelling in film in general (maxime dos' direction). in this way, his giselle can move entirely new, global audiences, a huge feat for any ballet or dance film. the moral? maybe only reimagine a classic tale if you are bringing something as spectacularly new to the game as mr. khan does here.

             "intersectionality

🇫🇷 coucou,
un extrait du recueil #desauteursautoeditessemobilisentcontreleharcelementderue 👍
il s’agit de la nouvelle « comédie réussie » de natalia vikhalevsky, une autrice québécoise 😊
cette histoire joue sur les apparences, vous serez surpris à plusieurs reprises !
en tout, 17 nouvelles et donc 17 voix pour s’exprimer sur le harcèlement dans les lieux publics envers des femmes, des couples homosexuels, des victimes du racisme, etc.
des genres et des tons différents.
il est en vente aux formats papier et ebook 📚
un immense merci à @lmedml.alouqua qui vous propose un rdv chronique + interview sur son blog chaque mardi 🙏
et merci encore à @marierosejoshua de nous avoir lus 😉
bonne journée 🌤
•••
📒 vous pouvez retrouver mes livres, les ajouter à votre pal et consulter des extraits sur les sites de lecture comme babelio, livraddict, booknode et goodreads à mon nom d’autrice s. n. lemoing 😊
🛍 ils sont disponibles gratuitement en emprunt avec amazon kindle ou à 2.99€ pour les romans et 0.99€ pour les histoires courtes au format ebook, et entre 8 et 11€ pour les versions papier 📖
•••
🇬🇧 hi,
an excerpt from a short story of the anthology about street harassment!
this novella is from our only quebec author & has several twists, things are never what they seem 😉
there’s a facebook page for the book. 17 novellas have been selected, 17 voices for women, queer people, people of color, etc. who have been harassed.
have a great time 🌤
•••
📚 if you love epic fantasy & badass female characters you can read more info about my writings in my bio. one of them has been acclaimed by 100+ literary bloggers 😊
🛍 my writings are available for free for kindle unlimited subscribers, as ebooks at 1,15$ or 0,99£, etc. & paperback for $14 👍

text:
1003 - 1010 - life drawing
last sunday i joined another life drawing session with sunday nudes. the model began with a dance and we sketched while she moved, which was different. all the other poses were of 15-20 minutes and my sketches alternate between a4 and a5 sizes. i was most pleased with my third (1005) drawing - or at least her legs! one sketch was done while we were having a discussion about the #metoo movement.
sun-10-feb-2019

text: #blackhistorymonth “with pen and voice: a critical anthology of nineteenth century african-american women” this is my literary bible and playbook for my activism. the strength, words and oratory genius of the women in this anthology not only empower me but makes my heart long for sages today. their prose are unmatched in today’s babble of slogans and cliches. their activism is fueled by observation, reflection and burden for the oppressed and not reactionary only. their protest is laced with spirituality, grace, and dignity. and, though they speak truth to power with force they leave no carnage in their path. they lace followers who are healers not dividers. “political life in our country has plowed in muddy channels, and needs the infusion of clearer and cleaners waters. i am not sure women are so much better than men that they will clear the stream by virtue of their womanhood: it is not through sex but through character that the best influence of women upon the life of the nation must be exerted.” frances ellen watkins harper (1891) perhaps  dr. king read these words to make his race analysis “not by the color of their skin but the content of their character.” thinking out loud; reading black history #blackwomensvoices #myblackhistory #ourblackhistory #wisdom #metoo #healthesexes #riseup #iammybrotherskeeper #cancelculture #iammysisterskeeper #blackhistorywithmed #iambecauseweare 💋 #sheabassador #irreverentmemoirofagrownasswoman

text:
budzisz się.wokól  dziwnie cicho.twoja córka sonia patrzy na ciebie przenikliwie smutnymi oczami.chcesz jej powiedzieć, że wszystko będzie dobrze,ale wiesz ,że to niemożliwe.na waszych rękach błyszczą opaski.ich widok pali cię  od środka.licznik ustawiony jest tylko na 100 słów dziennie.jego przekroczenie spowoduje wymierzenie ładunku elektrycznego w twoją dłoń.jak wytrzymasz milcząc? przeciętnie człowiek wypowiada w ciągu dnia 16 tyś. słów.nie możesz już prawie tego robić, nie mozesz  nawet czytać.książki to przecież słowa.  z kuchni dochodzi rozmowa twojego męża i synów. oni mogą mówić, oni są mężczyznami. wrócił patrarchiat.
jesteś w stanie wyobrazić sobie taką sytuację? jesteś w stanie uwierzyć, że wladza zamknie kobietom  prawie na zawsze usta i  pozbawi ich wolnej woli? zajrzyj do książki "vox".twoja przygoda w przerażającej dystopi dopiero się zaczyna.

szczerze polecam.

za książkę dziękuję @wydawnictwomuza

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
our ceo presented recently on medicine and social new media, and it's importance - and following this recent social media awareness we woke up to quite a few of our delegates' queries this morning asking why their account has lost a chunk of followers overnight.

the knee-jerk reaction is to think, was it something you said? likely not, unless you've backed beautician injectors or said the #metoo movement was a lot of fuss about nothing. so why then?

unless instagram confirm it, we won't know for sure - but they did the same think a few years ago and had an enormous purge of inactive, fake, bot or bought accounts. it explained that they had built machine learning tools to help identify accounts that use these services and remove inauthentic or inactive accounts.“this type of behaviour is bad for the community, and third-party apps that generate inauthentic likes, follows and comments violate our community guidelines and terms of use.”
if instagram identified an account as potentially fake, it sent an in-app message asking them to secure their account. and it appears that last night, accounts that hadn’t secured their account were removed - which explains the drop in follower numbers. @arianagrande lost 3m followers! don't worry.

if you had bots that were following you, you don't want them anyway. if it's a glitch you'll get them back. but it highlights what we've always said too about not buying followers. why? it's only for vanity. it's so obvious, and someday, somehow instagram will find out and delete them. you'll look far worse losing half your followers overnight, than any credence you got from looking popular. #fakefollowers #socialmedia #lostfollowers #instgrampurge #bots #followersdisappeared #wheredtheygo

text:
läste en artikel om indigenious kvinnor och icke-binäras utsatthet.
statistik visade på att natives i alaska och usa hade 2.5 större chans att bli utsatta för sexuella övergrepp än icke natives.
detta är ju dock inget som endast är ett problem i usa/kanada, utan artikeln menar på att urbefolkning i ex indien, filippinerna, myanmar och många fler länder hade samma problematik, och hur i vissa länder det användes våldtäkter strategiskt mot urbefolkningen.
rent generellt känner jag inte att detta är förvånande, urbefolkning har i oavsett land ofta varit förtryckt under andra, vilket i sin tur leder till att de får sämre vilkor, etc och inte sedda som jämlikar.

länk till artikel här: https://www.culturalsurvival.org/publications/cultural-survival-quarterly/indigenous-womens-rights-are-human-rights

#intedinfetisch #metoo #justice #metoosverige #metoosweden

text:
“faça um café, não faça guerra!” rss 
eu tomava café todas as manhãs ouvindo o boechat. meu ritual começou há 4 anos.

cresci nos anos 90, ouvindo e tentando mexer a cabeça com o fat family. e hoje faleceu a cantora do grupo, a deise cipriano.

adotei a cidade do rio de janeiro como minha. e em uma semana a vi sofrendo com duas tragédias.

o estado de minas, que mais “exporta” gente do bem, anda sofrendo com desastres provocados por descasos.

notícias de feminicídios todos os dias nos noticiários.
tudo muito triste! *eita.. cada dia que passa esse café tem ficado mais amargo! * 
não gostamos muito de lidar com emoções “ruins”. mas emoções são emoções!

querer que a vida seja feita somente de notícias boas e momentos felizes não condiz com a condição humana, de ser vivo.

sentir coisas ruins faz parte (ou melhor, deve fazer) da vida de todos. é a partir de frustrações que adquirimos o repertório de resiliência, de enfrentamento e resolução de problemas e outros.

não tô falando daquele papo motivacional de fazer “uma limonada se a vida lhe der um limão”. é algo muito mais complexo! 
é sentir todos os sabores (azedo, amargo, doce e salgado) e entender que eles vão se intercalando ao longo da vida.

e pra complicar mais nossa cabeça, às vezes eles vêm entrelaçados! 
se quiser entender melhor sobre seus sentimentos, pode contar comigo! 😉

text: "if you are a girl and you want to do a job that requires you to work for lengthy hours, you have the right to say no to the traditional ways. similarly, if you are a boy and you want to become a chef, you must have the freedom to become a chef. everyone must have the right to choose what they want, until and unless they are harming anyone else and that doesn't include harming their thinking or ego. so #inkaarkaro is a movement that gives you the right as children. i have a daughter, and i have been an advocate of educating our children about #sexualharassment. we must teach our children from the beginning about good touch & bad touch, about the boundaries of how someone can talk to you, and if someone does, it's not your mistake, you can and must stand up and say no to them and if you feel weak and vulnerable, then you must ask for help. and when they ask for help, we must stand by them." - @zhalay speaks about sexual harassment and empowering children from the beginning at #lahootimelo2019 #lahootimelo #lm2019 #lahooti #jamshoro #anodetowomen #odetowomen #metoo #zhalaysarhadi #abaurnahin

think about this for a moment. it's all i ask. watch this, and put yourself in his shoes. imagine if you had to take the life of the animals you ate. could you do it? would you do it? what if the the cow, chicken, pig or goat, that was part of your dinner recipe, came up to you after you gently called him over... and looked you in your eyes. he trusts you and believes you won't harm him. he wants to live. he has a family. he has friends. he has feelings and he has love to share. would you take the knife to his throat? ....
....
i didn't think so. so why do you pay someone else to do it? and when you pay someone else to do it, it is not happening in a room, by them selves... where it's quiet, calm, unsure surroundings.... it is happening it horrifying conditions, where they are forced to walk the plank to their death, hearing the screams of the friend ahead of them, smelling the blood of their loved ones. knowing that what happens next.... will not be good. 💔 
#repost @torontopigsave with @repostsaveapp ・・・ could you hold the knife?
💔🐷💔

#dennisprager, founder of #prageru, an american nonprofit that takes the best ideas from the best minds and distills them down to five focused minutes.⠀
⠀
❓did you read this quote thoroughly? if not, read it again, dear parents. if you're a high school student, how are you preparing yourself for your future education in college? have you thought of alternative paths you could take instead? if you're already in college, are you finding your values clashing with those of the universities? what are you doing to hold your ground? ⠀
⠀

⠀

become a member or leader!⠀
click the link on our bio for more info⠀

📣📣📣whether you’ve found a community on campus or not, trinicy exists to support you and be part of your community. we are primarily christ-followers before we identify with any other membership categories. this means that all christians - whether you are conservative or liberal or apolitical - are welcome to join and form and build this community. why? because we believe christians’ unity in christ is the only thing capable of bridging the cultural chasm in our land and withstanding the divide caused by powers and principalities.⠀
⠀

text:
raw moment- when i was 4 years old, i was snatched off my bike by a man who lived across the street from my grandparents house. his hand covered my mouth and he dragged me into his backyard through his side fence. he threatened to kill me if i didn’t open my mouth. i could hear my grandparents searching for me. he did horrific things which left me scarred in many ways more mentally than physically. my mouth and throat were hurt badly by him at the time. i couldn’t breathe.. this wasn’t the only time i experienced this kind of trauma. again that same year i experienced more and after that even more. i have done a ton of work to overcome the triggers and debilitating responses however, here i sit 36 years later and still up at 5:00am because i have a dentist appointment coming up this afternoon. each time i’m in that chair i shake uncontrollably as tears stream down my face. having to lay on my back with my mouth and throat exposed is absolutely terrifying. my entire body goes into a panic and the room spins. i was sexually assaulted as a young adult and twice by doctors as well which makes it more triggering because of the white coat the dentist wears. sometimes i reported it and sometimes i was so traumatized i didn’t. i  just want people to know that if you think the #metoo movement is stupid, if you question victims truth or their decision to tell or not, if you speak in a way that’s dismissive or worse, you shame victims, you’re hurting people who are already so hurt inside. please be careful. this is a touchy subject and i think we should all feel welcome to share our pain during moments like these and not feel afraid to be called a lib , dem, liar, attention seeker, or anything other than a fellow friend who is hurting 🙏🙏🙏. i need a couple extra prayers and it took me this long to reach out because of the things i’ve seen some of my own family and friends post in their political anger. can the metoo movement be off limits already🤦‍♀️??? and ptsd is real and not only with people who’ve been to war. sometimes war is in our neighbors backyard 🤷‍♀️
so this is my truth and only part of it. i hope this inspires someone else to reach out when they are struggling.

text:
meet our sister - ailbhe smyth
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
ailbhe smyth has been active in the irish women's movement since it existed, and has been present in every milestone accomplishment.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“in terms of what we got out of the interview, i would say i felt a sense of her enormous compassion and humility. ailbhe is an institution in the women's rights movement of ireland and what i really got a sense of was the enormous effort and strength of character it has taken to haul a once fundamentally regressive country to the vanguard of the women's movement,” says our journalist joe stensons.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
photo by adam masterson (@adammarkphotos)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#sistersofeurope #europe #feminism #metoo #women #womenempowerment

text:
today used to be an important day. i would make some eloquent speech about death, and the world, and how i needed a father. but i refuse this year. for years my worth and who i was, was seen to certain “family” members as who i was to a dead man. you had zero to do with my upbringing and who i am as a person. my mother and experience raised me. trial and error taught me to be as bold and kind and brave and caring as i am. my friends (who i’m lucky enough to not have enough digits to count them on) helped, and still are helping me through the hardest parts of my life. i was not raised by a man. i will never need a man. a man did not make me who i am. so after today, he will get honorable mention for giving me my curls and skin tone, but my experiences without his help gave me true life. thank you to my mother veronica call who did the best she could given her own traumas and demons. thank you to my siblings alexandrea mae call, wesley charlie hobbes and kenny for allowing me to have a hand in raising you and teaching me young how to be responsible. thank you to my ex husband who taught me to laugh and helped me realize i could have, and deserved more. thank you to my friends for holding me at my lowest parts of depression and still sticking by me regardless. thank you to every ex boyfriend for teaching me what i will not tolerate from a “man.” thank you to the lovers over the years, male, female, non binary, who have taught me trust. and to my father: i did not need you. i needed you to love my mother. you did and i came from it. so the only thing i will say about the man who helped give me my genes, is thank you for loving her. but past that, i did not need you.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
"the name gemma ward is synonymous with ‘00s fashion, a favourite of miuccia prada, who at her modelling height was said to be earning us$3million a year by the time she was 19. by 20, ward was trying her hand at acting starring in black balloon and pirates of the caribbean: on stranger tides. every major brand or magazine had tapped her as its face or cover model."
*
"in 2008, ward’s then boyfriend heath ledger passed away at 28 from what was reported to be an accidental overdose and the model returned to her native australia to grieve and disappear from the international modelling scene. fast forward to 2013 and ward and her partner david letts welcomed their first child, daughter naia, with their son jett born in 2017."
*
of her return and the changes she’s felt in the industry post the fashion industry’s #metoo moments:
*
"the industry is changing so i guess the thing that i’ve been appreciating about working now is working with new and different people and especially a lot of up and coming photographers and especially a lot of female photographers, it’s incredible.” *
"there’s more diversity. it’s more inclusive, it’s less snipey and negative and hateful. it’s just more positive, and more fun. it’s great, it’s moving in a positive direction,”
*

text:
“i’m ok.” this week, things are grinding to a halt. work feels too stressful, too useless, too harsh on my self-esteem. being away from home feels too difficult. getting out of bed in the morning feels like a great labour. the future feels overwhelming and punishing; everything feels pointless and i just can’t find a part of me that cares. i have escaped it all to stay at home and rest my mind. although i’m not sure of the solution right now, spending time alone with me seems to be all i feel capable of. ~copingdiary ~
~
~
~

text:
yes!!! a new episode of @wtfeminine podcast is out and ready for your ears!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen burris is an incredibly talented memphis artist! she's a singer, songwriter & performer who had used her art to work through some personal trauma. she needed a way to get it out and she found that through her music.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in this episode, jen opens up about being sexually assaulted back in college and the pain of not being believed by the people who are supposed to protect you the most.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
kim & jen also discuss the "me too" movement, what a real man looks like, and the importance of setting boundaries.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen also talks about the joy of being a mom and how growing up with an alcoholic & emotionally abusive mother has shaped her own approach to parenting.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
spoiler alert: sometimes our parents teach us the valuable lesson of what not to do as a parent.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
kim & jen also discuss all the exciting things on the horizon for jen including writing lyrics & collaborating with other local artists.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen is such a brave woman and this episode is for anyone who has experienced something incredibly painful and has come out on the other side stronger.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

yes!!! a new episode is out and ready for your ears!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen burris is an incredibly talented memphis aist! she's a singer, songwriter & performer who had used her a to work through some personal trauma. she needed a way to get it out and she found that through her music.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in this episode, jen opens up about being sexually assaulted back in college and the pain of not being believed by the people who are supposed to protect you the most.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
kim & jen also discuss the "me too" movement, what a real man looks like, and the impoance of setting boundaries.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen also talks about the joy of being a mom and how growing up with an alcoholic & emotionally abusive mother has shaped her own approach to parenting.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
spoiler ale: sometimes our parents teach us the valuable lesson of what not to do as a parent.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
kim & jen also discuss all the exciting things on the horizon for jen including writing lyrics & collaborating with other local aists.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
jen is such a brave woman and this episode is for anyone who has experienced something incredibly painful and has come out on the other side stronger.

text:
19那年（還是18？）因為沒考上政大哭得稀裡嘩啦，還被陳元浩超爛的安慰法安慰，後來好不容易喜歡上台中，然後命運轉了一圈卻又考上回來了，然後雙了日文，然後當了托福主考官，然後誤打誤撞進了喜歡但每天苦哈哈的地方煎熬的求生存。
一直努力往前跑著比包偉銘更勤奮，好像對未來很惶恐卻又抱著期待亦步亦趨被吸引著。
人生很複雜，但就像每天早起上班的路上勉勵自己那樣「生命會自己找到出路、荷蘭乳牛在初鹿、好萊塢那個叫#metoo」

text:
mesa launches podcast on #metoo movement
# (sara waite / sterling journal-advocate) boulder's moving to end sexual assault is launching a podcast as a way to increase its reach into the community. a news release from mesa stated that the podcast, called "sex: by invitation only," will launch with a series that poses the question "is it a scary time for men?" in the first episode, mesa will explore public opinion of boulder county residents on the issue that will be presented in the context of the #metoo movement. "follow us through the next five weeks where we will hear from both survivors of sexual violence and men who are challenging toxic masculinity," the news release stated. "we will examine who is being held accountable for their actions and hear about community programs focused on prevention of gender-based violence." the podcast is available at movingtoendsexualassault.org/media, podbean, google play and itunes. john bear: 303-473-1355, bearj@dailycamera.com or twitter.com/johnbearwithme original article source...

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text_retweet:
💘 some valentine's day consent thoughts 💘

how have you approached your desire? what habits do you have around expressing interest? can you stay present to and name your desire? does your desire bring you shame, does it slip out, taking hold in ways you struggle to control? 
are you using force, power, coercion, or manipulation to do what you want without attuning to the other? 
are you on autopilot? 
what story are you running?

are you present? 
does your desire match a want from them and what were the things that let you know?

what are the delicious things that enticed you, told you you were welcome?

what is your relationship to your desire and how do you honour what it has to tell you?
.
.
.
.

repost @abadsubject
• • • • •
we get so many variations of this question! it's a rich topic! how do we be flirty and respectful at the same time? it's definately possible though we acknowledge that it can be confusing considering the scewed up messages we get about conquest (yuck), dating and romance. let's push back on the idea (that we hear often tbh) that #metoo killed romance and flirting. it's sooo not true. flirting is great when its wanted and lifts us up.

text_retweet:
reposted from @thealphanursee -  thanks @msen_doo for nominating me.

my name is vivian nwogu, an empowered young woman that has empowered over #500 women directly and indirectly and i hope to do more by god's grace.

my story as an empowered woman will not be complete if i don't recognize the favour and mercy of god in my life, my mum and all my aunties who contributed in one way or the other.

my story started when i felt the need to make a change in the lives of young girls in the rural areas but i wasn't sure of the best way to go about it, i decided to just send messages to friends about it to see who will join me, among the people i sent the message to @mrs.a.c.e took it upon herself to spread the word so that more people will volunteer and donate and that led to the success of our very first outreach in @hygieneandhealthngo (pro-women safe sanitary foundation) thanks darling for what you dis as a friend, and to my entire alumni classmates of owerri girls secondary school, i can't thank you guys enough. when i needed more clearity, i contacted @victorugo of @mentallyawareng for help but because he stays far away in lagos he directed me to @preahgaza who turned out to become my friend and sister. i'm not forgetting all the advice i got from @gusitoby that helped me start @nursehubafrica which is really thriving now.

in the aspect of self development, @bukyshonibare showed up and taught me a lot of things, not forgetting @santishawalkerrn for the knowledge she impacted in me.

i will not end this without recognising my amazing coach @emilywalekoya who makes out time to coach me every week and give me awesome ideas on how to thrive. i hope to make you proud soon ma'am😘

and to every other woman that has in one way or the other empowered me, i want say thank you. i appreciate.

and @awloint for the privilege to be an ngfl.

i nominate @preshgaza.

#empoweredwomenempowerothers #empoweredforsustainability #awlcrwands2019 - #regrann

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
#خودت_باش_دختر
از باور کردن دروغ‌هایی که درباره‌تان گفته می‌شود دست بردارید تا تبدیل به همان کسی شوید که واقعا هستید. 
نوشتهٔ #ریچل_هالیس 
ترجمهٔ هدیه جامعی 
دخترها از سراسر دنیا از من می‌پرسن که چطور... چطور وقتی زمین می‌خورم دوباره بلند ‌شم؟ چطور توی زندگی‌م تغییر ایجاد ‌کنم؟ چطور با این ضربۀ روحی کنار بیام؟ چطور دوباره شروع کنم؟ چطور این بچه ها رو بزرگ کنم؟ سؤال‌هایی از این دست که از نظر من همه یک جواب دارند. 
بعضی از شماها حتماً از این یادداشت‌ها از من گرفتید... می‌گفتم که «تو یک مبارزی. خیلی قوی هستی. تو هر کاری که بخوای می‌تونی انجام بدی.» اما بعد از مدتی متوجه شدم اون جوابی که می‌خواستم رو نمی‌گفتم. اون‌وقت بود که سعی کردم کتابی بنویسم که جواب تمام سؤال‌های شما توش باشه، اگه دوست من بودید یا اگر خودم بودید؛ توی سن بیست، بیست‌وپنج، یا سی سالگی. 
و جواب اینه: تو قدرت تغییر زندگی‌ت رو داری. دیگه دنبال پاسخ سؤالاتت توی اینترنت نگرد. تو جواب رو می‌دونی. تو ابزارش رو داری. 
فکر کردم اگه این کتاب رو بنویسم و همۀ کشمکش‌های زندگی خودم رو توش بیارم، یا زمان‌هایی که نمی‌دونستم چه‌کار کنم و گیج بودم، وقت‌هایی که زمین خوردم، اشتباه ‌کردم؛ و اگه مسیری که خودم رفتم رو نشونتون بدم، اون‌وقت جرئتی بهتون می‌دم که توی مسیر خودتون هدفمند قدم بردارید. من نخواستم نظاره‌گر غرق شدن شما باشم. من توی محبت کردن آدم خشکی هستم، پس هرکس که مشکلش رو پیش من مطرح کنه باید پیه همه‌چیز رو به تنش مالیده باشه. می‌دونید، «من هم همین‌طور (#metoo)» از قدرتمندترین کلمات زبان انگلیسی هستند. و من از این تفکر یک بستر ساختم. و همچنین از این باور که «من اول شروع می‌کنم.» من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و راجع به افسردگی بعد از زایمانم حرف می‌زنم؛ راجع ‌به مصرف بیش از اندازۀ الکل، گرفتاری‌های ازدواجم، دشواری‌های بچه بزرگ‌کردنم، شرمساری از بدنم، سوءاستفاده و اهمال‌کاری و آسیب‌های دوران کودکی‌م. من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و اولین کسی می‌شم که بهتون می‌گه همۀ این اتفاق‌ها براش افتاده. و نه‌تنها این اتفاق‌ها رو تجربه کردم، بلکه تونستم با موفقیت ازشون گذر کنم. امیدوارم این کتاب جسارت انجام این کار رو به شما بده. امیدوارم وقتی داستان‌هام رو می‌شنوید و این کتاب رو می‌خونید بفهمید که تنها نیستید. پس به‌همین‌دلیل این کتاب رو نوشتم.

#دختر #دخترها #زنان #فمینیسم #قوی_بودن #اعتماد_به_نفس #مبارزه #خودت_باش #کتاب_کوله_پشتی #کوله_پشتی #برابری #تلاش

فکر کردم اگه این کتاب رو بنویسم و همۀ کشمکش‌های زندگی خودم رو توش بیارم، یا زمان‌هایی که نمی‌دونستم چه‌کار کنم و گیج بودم، وقت‌هایی که زمین خوردم، اشتباه ‌کردم؛ و اگه مسیری که خودم رفتم رو نشونتون بدم، اون‌وقت جرئتی بهتون می‌دم که توی مسیر خودتون هدفمند قدم بردارید. من نخواستم نظاره‌گر غرق شدن شما باشم. من توی محبت کردن آدم خشکی هستم، پس هرکس که مشکلش رو پیش من مطرح کنه باید پیه همه‌چیز رو به تنش مالیده باشه. می‌دونید، «من هم همین‌طور (#metoo)» از قدرتمندترین کلمات زبان انگلیسی هستند. و من از این تفکر یک بستر ساختم. و همچنین از این باور که «من اول شروع می‌کنم.» من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و راجع به افسردگی بعد از زایمانم حرف می‌زنم؛ راجع ‌به مصرف بیش از اندازۀ الکل، گرفتاری‌های ازدواجم، دشواری‌های بچه بزرگ‌کردنم، شرمساری از بدنم، سوءاستفاده و اهمال‌کاری و آسیب‌های دوران کودکی‌م. من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و اولین کسی می‌شم که بهتون می‌گه همۀ این اتفاق‌ها براش افتاده. و نه‌تنها این اتفاق‌ها رو تجربه کردم، بلکه تونستم با موفقیت ازشون گذر کنم. امیدوارم این کتاب جسارت انجام این کار رو به شما بده. امیدوارم وقتی داستان‌هام رو می‌شنوید و این کتاب رو می‌خونید بفهمید که تنها نیستید. پس به‌همین‌دلیل این کتاب رو نوشتم.

text:
i'd rather die 
to have my heart invaded, controlled, used.
to have my life in chains, pinned down, hemmed in. 
to have my choices made for me, my free will enclosed in cement.
to be under a boot, owned, oppressed.
to be used, lied to, beaten, abused.
to be down trodden, weak, afraid.
to reject all these things, is a rule i choose to live by.
to make my own way, i am not anyone's possession. 
because, to be all these things, i would rather die.
✒

to be used, lied to, beaten, abused.
to be down trodden, weak, afraid.
to reject all these things, is a rule i choose to live by.
to make my own way, i am not anyone's possession. 
because, to be all these things, i would rather die.
✒
✒
✒

text:
demo 8 mars för rätt till vård | "kvinnliga läkares förening håller på internationella kvinnodagen ett läkarmöte som handlar om vårdbehov och vårdtillgång för patienter med konsekvenser efter sexuella övergrepp.i samband med detta vill vi bjuda in till demonstration. vi som patienter samlas och visar att vi finns och att vi inte är nöjda med vården som den ser ut för oss idag. ta med dig vänner och anhöriga som stöd, vi behöver all uppslutning vi kan få! man behöver inte ha varit utsatt själv, demonstrationen är för alla som håller med om att de som utsatts för sexuella övergrepp har rätt till vård.

vi möts utanför läkarförbundet på villagatan 5 kl 15.30 och börjar demonstrationen kl 16.00. några plakat kommer att finnas, men ta gärna med egna. det kommer även finnas möjlighet att träffas veckan innan och göra plakat tillsammans. (mer info om plakatbygge och förslag på vad man kan skriva på dem kommer!) för dig som är intresserad av att stanna på läkarmötet:

läkarmötet startar kl 17.00, insläpp börjar 16.30. den första delen av mötet är öppen för allmänheten, efter pausen kommer endast läkare få vara kvar. 
under den första delen kommer hermine holm från rise och flo fermelin från patientföreningen medusa att vara med och prata ur patienternas perspektiv. gita rajan från wonsa kommer också vara där och prata om hur vården utvecklats för oss som patienter från 1800-talet och fram till idag.

här finns mer information om läkarmötet: https://slf.se/sveriges-kvinnliga-lakares-forening/nyheter/extra-lakarmote-8-mars-2019/ "

text:
🗣please go read the latest updates on the aj calloway case, there are a lot of lessons and takeaways from the alleged sexual assault accounts from these women. •••
🚨a couple reminders of safety tips i want to highlight for you:
1) trust your gut. 
when your intuition and gut is telling you to take a certain action or inaction trust it is for your good. even if it may appear someone else may say you are being difficult or killin their vibe, or you are being mean. 
sidenote:  if you are the friend don’t be scared to be assertive and make sure your girl “catches” your signal you are giving her, if you need to pull her to the side and express the gut feelings you are having that is okay to do 😉
➡️better their feelings be hurt, than you be hurt. 
2) sexual predators wear many faces. 
they can be famous or on television, and they can be unknown and work a “regular” job. they can be (and most of the time are) very nice, charming, they can be attractive, loved my many, have a family, and described as “not the type” to do such a thing.  predators don’t necessarily look a certain way, but they do behave in a certain way. 
don’t drop your guard because a man has money, is on tv, has a family, and “too much to lose” etc to do such a thing.  especially don’t drop it because they tell you “i won’t hurt you” “i won’t do anything to you!” 3) we over me!
there is power in numbers. if you came with your friends, then leave with your friends.  period. •
🚨if you have been attacked/assaulted please tell someone. go to the hospital immediately and ask to get a rape kit. 
there is a hotline that is 24/7 if you feel you have nobody to turn to, or do not know what to do. 📲 1-800-656-4673
•know that you do have power. just because you may have been overpowered and/or manipulated, does not mean an assaulter holds the cards. this is your life and you will get through this and thrive. you are not what has happened to you, you are not your  past!  and there are resources out here to assist you in your healing. 🙏🏾💪❤️

text:
india is full rapist, indian villages do what ever they want, and india does nothing, couples are paraded naked, raped, and murdered, every day, like aarav and sophia, rip.
-
-
on january 16, 2019, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, aarav, 19, and sophia, 18, got married and were cousins but there family, did not like it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, raped, and killed by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, raped and murder. rajasthan kept the names of the attack hidden. the attackers are only in jail for 3 years. shame on india, rip aarav and sophia.
-
-

"children are often not allowed to talk about sex, even if they see it in almost everything daily. we act as if it is not a topic that we should talk about. it is like an elephant in a room that everyone ignores but acknowledges its presence.  it is sad that many children get molested by close family members at a very tender age and they have to live with this for a very long time before they understand that what they went through was called "molestation" and that it is wrong."
.
.
.
●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●●
at what age should children be taught sex education? .
.
.
.

text:
it is a fucked up world for a woman, and here is why:
.
i am scared of traveling alone, i always think twice before choosing a destination and consider my safety as a solo “woman” traveler, and i mostly look for my “men” friends (the ones i share the hobby of mountains with) to travel with, or a group.
this time, as i couldn’t find travelers to the destination i wanted to go to, i decided to stay in the lebanese mountains and learn how to ski.
i booked a hotel , and asked my connections for a tutor.
.
so yesterday, i met my ski instructor and we headed to the beginners’ slope. after briefing about skis, how to wear them and put them on, he asked me how old i am. then he said my face is very beautiful. for the people who know the cedars’ beginners’ slope, it is a handle that you have to hold that it takes you up. it could be a bit intimidating for the first timers. so he embraced me from all sides and asked me to trust him. i was tense, i had no space, he said relax and started massaging my neck and shoulders. i couldnt do anything because i was stuck and i would possibly fall. i said firmly im here to ski and not for massage. 
as i followed his instructions he said after i know how to descend i should give him a kiss! i said no. he said not to take him seriously as he jokes alot, and most of his jokes are about how beautiful i am, and that he is making an effort not to say more.
he basically taught me everything except how to take the handle up the slope (i saw kids going up alone) he said it’s too dangerous for beginners. and of course on the way up as i am helpless he “mistakingly” slides his hands on my ass or my waist as he tells me that im beautiful.
..
he made this entire learning how to ski a disgusting experience and of course i fired him.
.
fuck those assholes.
.
thanks to my brother who dragged me to the slope the next day and showed me i can go up the slope by myself. but here we go again. i was safe because my brother was around. a woman is always a prey when alone.
.
.
.
#harrassment #metoo #abaad #womenrights #womenenpowerment #somemenaretrash

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitba doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subve elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
the nominee for best documentary is...“!women art revolution – a secret history” (2010)!
...
“‘!women art revolution’ is an inspiring documentary about the history of feminist art, poignantly told through the perspectives of artists, curators, and critics, including the guerrilla girls, lucy lippard, adrian piper, yvonne rainer, martha rosler, betye saar, carolee schneemann, nancy spero, and marcia tucker. mixing multiple visual strategies, lynn hershman leeson filmed her subjects over 40 years, overlaying her footage with political events such as the vietnam war, the civil rights movement, the black panthers, women’s liberation, and the free speech movement. the film acquires further urgency in light of today’s #metoo movement.” –#roxanamarcoci (@roxanamarcoci), senior curator in our department of photography
…
this awards season we’re celebrating the rich film history preserved in #momacollection. liven up your watchlist with our staff’s #momapicks: mo.ma/picks
…
[🎥: “!women art revolution – a secret history.” 2010. usa. directed by lynn hershman leeson. purchase from the artist, 2011. funded in part by the modern women's fund committee. purchase from zeitgeist films, 2015]

text:
when i arrived in alaska back in 2008 
i had no job. no permanent place to live
& just a little over $1000 to my name.
⠀⠀
the first investment i made was a $400 down-filled northface coat from rei, which i purchased from the sale of the car i used to drive from nj, across the country, through the yukon territory into alaska.
i walked to and from work, about a half mile, every day in the bitter cold and snow. when i first came to anchorage it was unseasonably warm.
⠀⠀
it didn’t last long.
⠀⠀
as the summer days faded into darkness and the snow covered the city, like a giant blanket, i quickly learned i was no longer in “kansas anymore.” once october came it had begun snowing steadily and i was told to expect that until may. 
i settled into a job & the fully furnished condo i found for rent with a roommate & my boyfriend. 
after work one night i came home to an empty house, or so i thought, as i struggled to find the switch on the wall in the dark, out of the emptiness he spoke.
i nearly jumped out of my skin.
i knew his mood by the tone in his voice. whatever i had walked into was about to play out. only i was all too familiar with how it did so i quickly removed myself. ⠀⠀
my story could have ended there. 
like it almost did years before, in another apartment, in another city, when one of his moods landed me unconscious. 
only it didn’t. ⠀⠀
i am standing here today. no longer in alaska. no longer with a man that abused me for nearly five years because someone i never met breathed life back into me when i didn’t think i could find the strength on my own. ⠀⠀
as i stand here today, watching my girls play, i am reminded of god’s amazing grace. how he has washed me clean like snow & given me new life. 
i have learned that survival doesn’t take place until well after you’ve been out of that horror you were living in. and the residual will kill you just the same. so i’ve finally decide maybe i should just let that shizz go, only trauma doesn’t necessarily work that way. #metoo #survivor #ipreview

i knew his mood by the tone in his voice. whatever i had walked into was about to play out. only i was all too familiar with how it did so i quickly removed myself. ⠀⠀
my story could have ended there. 
like it almost did years before, in another apament, in another city, when one of his moods landed me unconscious. 
only it didn’t. ⠀⠀
i am standing here today. no longer in alaska. no longer with a man that abused me for nearly five years because someone i never met breathed life back into me when i didn’t think i could find the strength on my own. ⠀⠀
as i stand here today, watching my girls play, i am reminded of god’s amazing grace. how he has washed me clean like snow & given me new life. 
i have learned that survival doesn’t take place until well after you’ve been out of that horror you were living in. and the residual will kill you just the same. so i’ve finally decide maybe i should just let that shizz go, only trauma doesn’t necessarily work that way.

text:
i did a little presentation of some new work yesterday. these are 8 plexiglass panels, parts painted and parts drawn, and together they tell the story of medusa from her own perspective. it’s not widely known that she wasn’t always a stone-turning ‘monster’. actually, she was athena’s priestess, but after she got raped by poseidon, athena turned her back on her and turned her into a gorgon. this kind of story, with resonances of abuse and victim blaming, and the way the story has been told to us... well. it seems more contemporary than ever. so these panels are a hymn to her, a retelling, a queering, a piece of comic poetry. `

detailed shots of the individual pieces will come soon! hope you enjoy, as always :) #medusa #mythology #queering #comicpoetry 
#artschool #drawing #painting #plexiglass #layers #metoo #hymn #historyishisstory

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text: okay, since my last one was of someone i liked but didn't love, just because i needed to fill the space, let me make it clear -- if i had an action script to sell (and i don't really do that anymore), i would want it to go to lexi alexander. she knows how to shoot a fight scene, partly because she's a great director, partly because she's a fighter herself, having been a karate and kickboxing champion. she made what i still consider the best of the marvel movies (okay, top five) in "punisher war zone," the most transgressively hilarious action movie since "robocop," or maybe the original "dawn of the dead." her "green street hooligans" is pretty amazing, too, made me believe elijah wood is a bad ass. she is an essential twitter follow (@lexialex) and once told me there that her long short "johnny flynton" is her best work. so i watched it yesterday. and it's very good, taking all the boxing cliches and making them new. but i think she's selling herself short. she's progressed with each movie, each better than the last. due (i believe) to her outspoken position in the #metoo movement (again, follow her on twitter), she's been relegated to tv directing lately, but i'm waiting for her to be rediscovered by hollywood. it'll probably take a smaller feature that breaks out, and i'd give a toe to help. i've tried directing action before, and i'd love to see how she does it.
name: Pete Barnstrom
tweet_full: okay, since my last one was of someone i liked but didn't love, just because i needed to fill the space, let me make it clear -- if i had an action script to sell (and i do not really do that anymore), i would want it to go to lexi alexander. she knows how to shoot a fight scene, partly because she's a great director, partly because she's a fighter herself, having been a karate and kickboxing champion. she made what i still consider the best of the marvel movies (okay, top five) in "punisher war zone," the most transgressively hilarious action movie since "robocop," or maybe the original "dawn of the dead." her "green street hooligans" is pretty amazing, too, made me believe elijah wood is a bad ass. she is an essential twitter follow (@lexialex) and once told me there that her long short "johnny flynton" is her best work. so i watched it yesterday. and it is very good, taking all the boxing cliches and making them new. but i think she's selling herself short. she's progressed with each movie, each better than the last. due (i believe) to her outspoken position in the #metoo movement (again, follow her on twitter), she's been relegated to tv directing lately, but i am waiting for her to be rediscovered by hollywood. it'll probably take a smaller feature that breaks out, and i'd give a toe to help. i have tried directing action before, and i'd love to see how she does it.

text:
it's been a tough year for us, both men and women. we have seen so much new events, that we can start a new channel of web-series for everyone to go gaga over. section 377, #metoo, several spoken (and many unknown) stories of violence, assault what not. it is the year where your tinder profile must be more attractive than your personality or cv, where the number of your instagram followers will dictate your coolness, rather than the other way around. putting snaps behind the wheel of a car, or your drinking escapades in clubs is more acceptable than watching romantic comedies, with popcorn and tears in your eyes (yes). despite all this social savagery, which is one of the several evils in this world, good people exist. and yes many cross the line to the other side; but the only way to cure this is not mental brainwashing, but love and conversation. time with friends and family, celebrating moments without worrying of the past and future. it is in the moment.

so this valentine's day, why not thank those who we truly love, rather than someone we just lust over for their profile pictures.

i love my family, who doesn't give up on me. my friends of school, who are still in touch, who taught me friendship goals for real. my college buds, for being the living testament of memes and memories. my crushes and heartbreaks (too many to mention here). i thank my worldly possessions which make me happy. 
and most importantly - i thank god - who continues to look after me, despite my flaws. 
happy valentine's day everyone!

#love #laugh #live #life #crush #heart #memories #heartbreaks #heartthrobs #romance #fun #friends #family #flaws #happiness #gratitude #valentinesday

text:
women have many more causes for loose skin than men... 👧🏽puberty causes the sudden growth of boobs, hips and bums. sometimes we don’t keep all those curves and can be left with skin less tight and firm
🤰 pregnancy stretches the stomach area to a great extent, and most women will not spring back to how their skin looked before
💊 hormones from birth control can cause weight fluctuations, quite significantly for some women

on a more generic note, any large loss of size/weight can lead to loose skin. it’s rare that a woman at some stage in her life won’t deal with one of these things! 
it is normal. you are not on your own.

text:
it's worth revisiting this past post because it has come up in conversation a lot recently.  let's talk about code switching. it's something millions of people think about every day. if you've never thought about it or even heard the term, you're probably in a position of privilege.  it's worth doing some research in to this topic if you're not familiar.⠀ . . . ⠀
every single day, people in marginalized groups have to put on a different persona just to be accepted in the workplace. they have to tone themselves down, change their hair, their way of communicating, all of it. and let's unpack that "being accepted in the workplace." what that really means, is making themselves more palatable to the dominant groups in the workplace, to make the dominant group more comfortable. ⠀
. . .⠀
yes, probably most companies that say they want people to bring their "authentic selves" to work are sincere. but as with most well-intentioned culture initiatives, they can fall short on-the-ground. and at the end of the day, it's the impact that matters much more than intent.  so do you really mean "bring your authentic self" for everyone? have you ever thought about the code switching that might still be required for your team to "bring their authentic selves"?⠀
. . . ⠀
it's time to re-examine everything we think we know about our company culture.  if we can't create safe spaces in our workplace for everyone, we don't have the right to talk about anything else.⠀
. . . ⠀
#hruprise #timesup #metoo #hrmustdobetter #whereishr #bethechange #codeswitching #company #culture #hr #authenticself #beanally #diversity #inclusion

text:
hey all, 
in case ur wondering what kind of account this is, and what kind of person is behind it, let me introduce myself and the reason i made this account; 
my name is amy and i am 20 years old. 
i got diognozed with ptsd after being raped a few months ago. 
because i don’t really talk to people about what happened,and the results of what happened, i just really feel the need to talk and interact with people who are going through (or have been through) something similar. 
i made this anonymous account because i want to be able to speak freely and openly about my story and my battle, without people from my direct enviroment judging me. 
i’m hoping that, through this account, i will not only feel empowered myself, but also be able to empower others who are fighting ptsd or another mental illness. 
please message me if you’d like to get in touch 🦋

p.s. please don’t mind any grammar or spelling mistakes as english isn’t my first language.

#ptsd #ptsdawareness #metoo #recovery #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness #rapesurvivor
#empoweringwomen

"princesa inca", óleo cuzqueño de autor anónimo y de mediados de 1800, donado al museo de arte de denver por la dra. belinda straight en 1996.
